How can we measure the direction of movement using an IMU ? - ResearchGate
Model Fusion for Inertial-based Personal Dead Reckoning Systems (PDF Download Available)

Can you try to compensate for offset in Accelerometer (X-direction) output signal and integrate it over time ?

This would result in either positive or negative velocity which is nothing but 180 or -180 degree movement.

The problem which I can see is the integration error which constantly integrates the drift/noise of the sensor. Any suggestions to eliminate this ?

If it is just categorial question (forward backward) anwers is quite simple - you could look at the sign of accelerometer reading in particular axis. But if you want to get exact orientation you need to use some orientation filter, look at the filter we have used in  our paper here: https://www.researchgate.net/publication/271850942_Model_Fusion_for_Inertial-based_Personal_Dead_Reckoning_Systems
